article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- — Ty Johnson's 30 points led UC Davis past Hawaii 75-63 on Thursday night. Johnson was 11 of 16 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 7 from the line for the Aggies (17-12, 12-6 Big West Conference). Elijah Pepper scored 30 points while going 9 of 17 from the floor, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and 10 for 11 from the line. Kane Milling was 2 of 8 shooting (1 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with six points. Bernardo da Silva finished with 20 points for the Rainbow Warriors (16-13, 8-9). Justin McKoy added nine points and nine rebounds for Hawaii. In addition, Noel Coleman had eight points. UC Davis plays UCSD on the road on Thursday, and Hawaii visits UC Riverside on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
